course - Complete Playwright test automation course with TypeScript. Best practices, API testing, Page Objects, Advanced features

Commands to push new updates: 
git add . - Stages all your changed files
git commit -m "message" - Commits with a description of what you changed
git push - Pushes to GitHub

Install playwright
npm init playwright@latest - Tyscript as default language.
Node folder => library and components
TEst Folder = test file. convention specs.ts.
.gitignote folder = ignre all uncomitted files
pkge.jason = describe project and script and libraries
playwright.config.ts = settings for the playwrtight (browsers...)

Cmmands
npx playwright test =>  run test
npx playwright show-report => show report in html
npx playwright test --project=chromium => run chrome tests only
npx playwright test example.spec.ts --project=chromium  => run one file only tests only
npx playwright test -g "has title" --project=chromium  => run one test only tests only
test.skip => ignore the test
test.only => ignore other tests
npx playwright test --ui  => for debugging with screenshots only
npx playwright test --trace on => report with trqce section
npx playwright test --debug  => execute test step by step on clic with brower


